    "abstract": "<jats:title>SUMMARY</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>\n                  Children infected with severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 (SARS-CoV-2) develop less severe coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19) than adults. The mechanisms for the age-specific differences and the implications for infection-induced immunity are beginning to be uncovered. We show by longitudinal multimodal analysis that SARS-CoV-2 leaves a small footprint in the circulating T cell compartment in children with mild/asymptomatic COVID-19 compared to adult household contacts with the same disease severity who had more evidence of systemic T cell interferon activation, cytotoxicity and exhaustion. Children harbored diverse polyclonal SARS-CoV- 2-specific na\u00efve T cells whereas adults harbored clonally expanded SARS-CoV-2-specific memory T cells. More na\u00efve interferon-activated CD4\n                  <jats:sup>+</jats:sup>\n                  T cells were recruited into the memory compartment and recovery was associated with the development of robust CD4\n                  <jats:sup>+</jats:sup>\n                  memory T cell responses in adults but not children. These data suggest that rapid clearance of SARS-CoV-2 in children may compromise their cellular immunity and ability to resist reinfection.\n                </jats:p>\n                <jats:sec>\n                  <jats:title>HIGHLIGHTS</jats:title>\n                  <jats:list list-type=\"bullet\">\n                    <jats:list-item>\n                      <jats:p>Children have diverse polyclonal SARS-CoV-2-specific na\u00efve T cells</jats:p>\n                    </jats:list-item>\n                    <jats:list-item>\n                      <jats:p>Adults have clonally expanded exhausted SARS-CoV-2-specific memory T cells</jats:p>\n                    </jats:list-item>\n                    <jats:list-item>\n                      <jats:p>Interferon-activated na\u00efve T cells differentiate into memory T cells in adults but not children</jats:p>\n                    </jats:list-item>\n                    <jats:list-item>\n                      <jats:p>Adults but not children develop robust memory T cell responses to SARS-CoV-2</jats:p>\n                    </jats:list-item>\n                  </jats:list>\n                  <jats:fig id=\"ufig1\" position=\"float\" orientation=\"portrait\" fig-type=\"figure\">\n                    <jats:graphic xmlns:xlink=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\" xlink:href=\"478400v1_ufig1\" position=\"float\" orientation=\"portrait\"/>\n                  </jats:fig>\n                </jats:sec>",
